# Code Owners

This file defines code ownership and approval requirements for the Malnu Kananga School Management System.

## Global Owner

`@sulhicmz`

## Business Domain Owners

### School Management (`app/Http/Controllers/Api/SchoolManagement/`)

```
# All school management controllers
app/Http/Controllers/Api/SchoolManagement/*
```

### Attendance Management (`app/Http/Controllers/Attendance/`)

```
# All attendance controllers
app/Http/Controllers/Attendance/*
```

### Calendar Management (`app/Http/Controllers/Calendar/`)

```
# All calendar controllers
app/Http/Controllers/Calendar/*
```

### Authentication (`app/Http/Controllers/Api/AuthController.php`)

```
# Authentication controller
app/Http/Controllers/Api/AuthController.php
```

### Core Infrastructure (`app/`)

```
# Core application infrastructure
app/Models/
app/Services/
app/Traits/
```

### Database (`database/`)

```
# All database migrations and configurations
database/migrations/*
database/seeders/*
config/database.php
```

### Configuration (`config/`)

```
# Application configuration files
config/*
```

### Documentation (`docs/`)

```
# All documentation files
docs/*
```

### Security (`app/Http/Middleware/`, `app/Traits/InputValidationTrait.php`)

```
# Security middleware and validation
app/Http/Middleware/*
app/Traits/InputValidationTrait.php
```

### Testing (`tests/`)

```
# All test files
tests/*
phpunit.xml
```

## Approval Requirements

| Area | Required Reviewers | Notes |
|-------|-------------------|-------|
| Authentication | @sulhicmz | Critical security area |
| School Management | @sulhicmz | Student, teacher management |
| Attendance | @sulhicmz | Leave, staff attendance |
| Calendar | @sulhicmz | Events, scheduling |
| Security Middleware | @sulhicmz | Auth, rate limiting, CSRF |
| Models | @sulhicmz | Core business models |
| Services | @sulhicmz | Business logic services |
| Database | @sulhicmz | Migrations, seeders |
| Configuration | @sulhicmz | Environment configs |
| Documentation | @sulhicmz | API guides, architecture |

## Notes

- Owners can be individuals, teams, or groups (defined using `@username` or `@team`)
- To add a new owner, add them to the appropriate section above
- Use `*` as a wildcard to match all files (e.g., `*.php` matches all PHP files)
- This file follows GitHub CODEOWNERS syntax: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-health-settings-with-code-owners/

## Updates

When adding new business domains or major areas, update this file to include:
- Domain controller directories
- Model directories  
- Service classes
- API routes

## Special Rules

- Security changes (SECURITY.md, middleware, auth) always require @sulhicmz review
- Database schema changes always require @sulhicmz review
- Critical bugs always require @sulhicmz review
